description:
With its original slightly racy lyrics, here’s the title song from Cole Porter’s musical hit “Anything Goes,” which starred Ethel Merman and ran for 420 performances on Broadway.

Transferred from the original 78rpm: Victor 24770 - Anything Goes (Porter) by Paul Whiteman and his Orchestra, vocal by Ramona, recorded October 26, 1934

THE 1935 HITS ARCHIVE - a collection of commercial recordings and songs that proved popular during the calendar year 1935 (some were recorded in 1934) via sales, sheet music, and radio exposure.…plus some others that have gained increased recognition or have been shown to have had an impact during the decades that followed.
